|volume=130 |issue=1 |pages=140–141 |year=2007 |month=January |pmid=16580119 |doi=10.1016/j.ejogrb.2006.02.010 |url=}}</ref> are examples of SERMs. Menerba, a botanically derived selective estrogen receptor beta agonist currently under development by [[Bionovo]], works like a SERM, but only activates on the estrogen receptor beta.
